The immediate past chairman of Shooting Stars Football Club (3SC) of Ibadan, Hon. Gbolagade Busari is dead. DAILY POST gathered that Busari fondly known as Buso died on Monday. He died at the University College Hospital (UCH), Ibadan. It was gathered that he would be buried later today. DAILY POST learnt that the deceased is a native of Ibadan. Busari had also served as Special Adviser to former Governor, late Abiola Ajimobi. Chairman, Sports Writers Association of Nigeria(SWAN) Oyo State chapter, Comrade Adeniyi Alebiosu, confirmed the death of the deceased. Alebiosu said, “It is sad and painful to announce the death of former Executive Chairman, Shooting Stars Sports Club, Gbolagade Busari. “He died early this morning at UCH, and will be buried today, according to Muslim rites.